<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17671209-44">
               <interp inst="t17671209-44" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17671209-44" type="year" value="1767"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17671209-44" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17671209"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17671209-44" type="date" value="17671209"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17671209-44-off234-c295" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-defend381 t17671209-44-off234 t17671209-44-verdict238"></join>
         
               <p>53. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17671209-44-defend381" type="defendantName">
                     Peter 
                     Wigginson 
                  <interp inst="t17671209-44-defend381" type="surname" value="Wigginson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-defend381" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-defend381" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17671209-44-off234" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-off234" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-off234" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing 50 pounds, weight of butter, value 10 s. and one wooden firkin, value one penny
            </rs>, the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17671209-44-victim383" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Pearson 
                  <interp inst="t17671209-44-victim383" type="surname" value="Pearson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-victim383" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-victim383" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-off234 t17671209-44-victim383"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17671209-44-cd235" type="crimeDate">Nov. 26</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-off234 t17671209-44-cd235"></join>. *</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17671209-44-person384">
                  John 
                  Pearson 
               <interp inst="t17671209-44-person384" type="surname" value="Pearson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person384" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person384" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t17671209-44-viclabel236" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-victim383 t17671209-44-viclabel236"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t17671209-44-crimeloc237">Prescot street, Goodman's-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17671209-44-crimeloc237" type="placeName" value="Prescot street, Goodman's-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17671209-44-crimeloc237" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-off234 t17671209-44-crimeloc237"></join>. It is customary, for want of room, to set two or three firkins out at the door; my wife missed one about candlelight, I happened to take the right way; I found the prisoner stopped by 
               <persName id="t17671209-44-person385">
                  Stephen 
                  Jones 
               <interp inst="t17671209-44-person385" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person385" type="given" value="Stephen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             at the corner of Chambers's street, in Lemon-street; he had the firkin, there was above 50 pounds weight of butter in it my property; I laid hold of the prisoner, and Jones brought the butter back to my shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17671209-44-person386">
                  Stephen 
                  Jones 
               <interp inst="t17671209-44-person386" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person386" type="given" value="Stephen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-person386" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carman; I was going with a load of flour, and stopped the prisoner with a firkin of butter; he was running, made me suspect him; I kept him till the prosecutor came.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I got the butter in the middle of the road; I was going to carry it back to show the carman where I found it, when the prosecutor came.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17671209-44-verdict238" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-verdict238" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17671209-44-punish239" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17671209-44-punish239" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17671209-44-defend381 t17671209-44-punish239"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>See him tried for a burglary, No 373, in the last Mayoralty.</p>
            </div1>
